HB 4004-14
(LC 242)
2/9/26 (ASD/gpb/ps)
Requested by HOUSE COMMITTEE ON AGRICULTURE, LAND USE, NATURAL RESOURCES,
AND WATER (at the request of Representatives Ken Helm, Mark Owens)
PROPOSED AMENDMENTS TO
HOUSE BILL 4004
1 On page 1 of the printed bill, line 2, after “308A.707” insert “, 536.032 and
2 537.623”.
3 On page 2, after line 29, insert:
4 “SECTION 4. ORS 536.032 is amended to read:
5 “536.032. Subject to confirmation by the Senate in the manner provided
6 in section 4, Article III, Oregon Constitution, the Governor shall appoint a
7 Water Resources Director. The director shall be an individual qualified by
8 training and experience and shall serve for a term of four years at the
9 pleasure of the Governor. The director [or a principal assistant] must [be]
10 ensure that a registered engineer experienced in water-related engineering
11 is employed by the Water Resources Department to carry out the
12 department’s functions under ORS 540.443 to 540.491.
13 “SECTION 5. ORS 537.623 is amended to read:
14 “537.623. (1) Notwithstanding ORS chapter 537, 540 or 541, a proposed
15 final order issued by the Water Resources Department under ORS chapter
16 537, 540 or 541 for an application requesting that the department approve a
17 new water right or a change to an existing water right or permit, registra-
18 tion or license, shall become, without further department action, a final or-
19 der as a matter of law 33 days after the close of the time period for
20 submitting a protest if:
21 “(a) The department includes a provision in the proposed final order ex-

1 plaining that the proposed final order will become a final order under this
2 section; and
3 “(b) A protest is not timely received by the department [within the 33
4 days].
5 “(2) Notwithstanding subsection (1) of this section, the department may
6 withdraw a proposed final order for reconsideration and issuance of a su-
7 perseding proposed final order not more than 33 days after the close of the
8 time period for submitting a protest.
9 “SECTION 6. (1) The Water Resources Department shall promote
10 and facilitate enrollment in the federal Conservation Reserve En-
11 hancement Program (132 Stat. 4534, 16 U.S.C. 3831a) for water users in
12 this state who voluntarily cancel ground water rights in areas where
13 the department is not allowing new rights to use ground water for ir-
14 rigation.
15 “(2) To carry out the provisions of subsection (1) of this section, the
16 department may enter into grant agreements and contracts and issue
17 direct payments to program enrollees.”.
18 In line 30, delete “4” and insert “7”.
19
